  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      We plan to study patient who faint in response to the sight of blood and compare them to
      healthy subjects who do not. We are going to use a special type of MRI scan (functional MRI)
      to determine if there are differences in brain activation in response to seeing bloody or
      gory pictures that occur before the fainting occurs.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Another aim of the study is to determine whether or not differences in personality traits
      among people with blood phobia is associated with differences in BOLD signal responses during
      fMRI.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
